        "retrievalContexts": [
          "Phishing Attacks in Healthcare (MediSure Health Systems)\n\nAutomatically locks compromised accounts when suspicious login activity is detected.\nUses AI to block malicious emails before they reach employees.",
          "Social Engineering in Banking (FinTrust Banking Solutions)\n\nDetects fraudulent access attempts and initiates immediate account lockdowns.\nAutomatically revokes administrative privileges if unauthorized actions are detected.",
          "IoT Security in Robotics (NovaTech Robotics)\n\nShuts down compromised robotic systems to prevent sabotage.\nDeploys security patches automatically to prevent further exploits.\n",
          "Credential Stuffing in Streaming Services (StreamView Entertainment)\n\nBlocks mass login attempts from unauthorized locations.\nForces password resets for accounts that show unusual login behavior.",
          "Examples of Good Responses:\nHow does Automated Incident Response work?\n\n\"Automated Incident Response uses AI to detect threats and take immediate action, such as blocking unauthorized access or quarantining a compromised device before damage spreads.\"\nWhat vulnerabilities does it address?\n\n\"It is especially effective against phishing, social engineering, and credential stuffing. If an attacker tries to use stolen credentials, the system can lock the account before any harm is done.\"\nHow can I apply this to my risk assessment?\n\n\"If your company scenario involves weak passwords, Automated Incident Response could immediately reset compromised accounts and notify affected users, reducing the risk of unauthorized access.\""
